# ============================================================================
# QuaiDirect Environment Variables Template
# ============================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# 1. NEVER commit your actual .env file to Git
# 2. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 3. Fill in your actual values in .env
# 4. For production deployments, use Lovable Cloud Secrets instead
#
# SECURITY WARNING:
# If you previously committed a .env file with real keys, you MUST rotate
# those keys immediately as they remain in Git history.
# See SECURITY.md for key rotation instructions.
#
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (Required)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get these values from your Supabase project settings:
# https://app.supabase.com -> Your Project -> Settings -> API
#
# The project ID (also in the URL)
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=your_supabase_project_id_here
#
# The public/anon key (safe to use in frontend, protected by RLS)
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_supabase_publishable_anon_key_here
#
# Your project's API URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE MAPS API (Required for map functionality)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create an API key at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 
# Required APIs to enable in Google Cloud Console:
# - Maps JavaScript API
# - Places API (for address autocomplete)
# - Geocoding API (for address to coordinates conversion)
#
# SECURITY: Restrict this key to your domain(s) in Google Cloud Console
# For Lovable deployments, add: *.lovableproject.com/*
#
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FIREBASE CLOUD MESSAGING (Required for push notifications)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get these from Firebase Console:
# https://console.firebase.google.com -> Your Project -> Project Settings -> General
#
# Firebase API Key (Web API Key)
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key_here
#
# Firebase Project ID
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_firebase_project_id_here
#
# Firebase Auth Domain (usually: your-project-id.firebaseapp.com)
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
#
# Firebase Messaging Sender ID (found in Cloud Messaging tab)
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id_here
#
# Firebase App ID (from Firebase SDK setup)
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_firebase_app_id_here
#
# Firebase Storage Bucket (usually: your-project-id.firebasestorage.app)
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.firebasestorage.app

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VAPID KEYS (Required for Web Push Notifications)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generate VAPID keys with: npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
#
# Public key (safe to use in frontend)
VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=your_vapid_public_key_here

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SENTRY (Optional - for error tracking in production)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your DSN from: https://sentry.io -> Your Project -> Settings -> Client Keys (DSN)
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn_here

# ============================================================================
# BACKEND / EDGE FUNCTIONS SECRETS (Configure in Supabase Dashboard)
# ============================================================================
#
# These secrets are NOT prefixed with VITE_ and should be configured in:
# Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> Edge Functions -> Secrets
#
# DO NOT add these to your local .env file (they are server-side only)
#
# Required Backend Secrets:
# ------------------------
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_... or sk_test_...
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# LOVABLE_API_KEY=... (if using Lovable integrations)
# INTERNAL_FUNCTION_SECRET=... (for securing internal edge function calls)
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=... (if using SMS notifications)
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=...
# TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=...
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_SERVER=... (separate key for server-side geocoding)
#
# Auto-configured by Supabase:
# ---------------------------
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (automatically available in edge functions)
# SUPABASE_URL (automatically available in edge functions)
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# LOVABLE CLOUD SECRETS CHECKLIST
# ============================================================================
#
# When deploying to Lovable Cloud, configure these secrets in:
# Lovable Dashboard -> Your Project -> Secrets
#
# Frontend Secrets (VITE_* prefix):
# ✓ VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# ✓ VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID
# ✓ VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# ✓ VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (⚠️ Use a NEW key if old one was exposed)
# ✓ VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID
# ✓ VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET
# ✓ VITE_SENTRY_DSN (optional)
#
# Backend Secrets (configure in Supabase Dashboard):
# ✓ STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
# ✓ STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# ✓ RESEND_API_KEY
# ✓ LOVABLE_API_KEY (if needed)
# ✓ INTERNAL_FUNCTION_SECRET
# ✓ TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID (if using SMS)
# ✓ TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN (if using SMS)
# ✓ TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER (if using SMS)
# ✓ GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_SERVER (if needed for server-side)
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in all required values in .env
# 3. Never commit your .env file
# 4. Verify with: git status (should not show .env)
#
# Lovable Cloud Deployment:
# 1. Configure all VITE_* secrets in Lovable Dashboard
# 2. Configure backend secrets in Supabase Dashboard
# 3. Test each secret is properly loaded
# 4. Rotate any previously exposed keys
#
# Key Rotation (if keys were exposed):
# 1. See SECURITY.md for detailed instructions
# 2. Generate new keys in respective service dashboards
# 3. Update Lovable Cloud Secrets
# 4. Update Supabase Edge Function Secrets
# 5. Delete/revoke old keys
#
# For more information, see:
# - docs/LOVABLE_CLOUD_SECRETS.md (comprehensive secrets guide)
# - SECURITY.md (security policies and key rotation)
# - docs/CONFIGURATION_CHECKLIST.md (deployment checklist)
#
# ============================================================================
